
Overview of verb instruct

The verb instruct has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (9) teach, learn, instruct -- (impart skills or knowledge to; "I taught them French"; "He instructed me in building a boat")
2. (9) instruct -- (give instructions or directions for some task; "She instructed the students to work on their pronunciation")
3. instruct, apprise, apprize -- (make aware of; "Have the students been apprised of the tuition hike?")
